</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="3000">3. Sets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Imagine you sell football uniforms, consisting of jerseys, shorts and socks.
Wouldn’t it be great if end customers could put together their own uniforms?
In other words, if they could choose the appropriate colour and size for each component?
Item sets make it possible!</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A set consists of multiple items (jersey, shorts, socks).
While placing an order, the end customer chooses the appropriate variation (colour, size) for each item.
It might help you to sketch out the items and variations that will be included in your set.</p>
</div>
