<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="4450">3.5. Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h3>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>I created a set but I can’t select a price. What should I do?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A set <em>does not have a fixed price</em> that you define yourself.
Rather, plentymarkets checks the price of each individual component and then calculates the cheapest possible price for the entire set.
Example: "Available from €99.99".</p>
</div>
<h5 id="_configuring_set_prices" class="discrete">Configuring set prices</h5>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/settings/prices#200">Create a sales price for sets</a>.</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>While doing so, specify that the type is a <strong>Set price</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/settings/prices#900">Link this sales price</a> to all of the components and enter a monetary price for each component. Note that the set components are normal variations.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional</em></strong>: It’s possible to make a set cheaper than the sum of its components. There are two ways to do this:</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>On the one hand, you could save lower monetary prices for the set sales price than for the normal sales price.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On the other hand, you could enter a <a href="/en/item/use-cases/combining-products#4000">percentage of discount</a> that applies to the entire set.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Can I control the order in which the components are displayed in the plentyShop?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There is not currently a setting to control which component is displayed first, second, third, etc.
However, we’re planning to implement a position field in the future.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><em>Workaround</em></strong>:
Add the components in whichever order they should be displayed in the plentyShop.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
